data.description:
''Washington Square'' is a beautiful 1920's residence on almost-an-acre of level landscaped grounds framed by a handsome brick wall.   Delightful location, just a few blocks to the Farmers market, the Horse District, and the shops along Park Avenue.

This home brings to life all of the joys of life in an historic home: high ceilings, wood floors, large rooms, handsome woodwork, and grand doorways. 

A wide covered porch wraps around two sides of the residence, offering true Southern charm as well as protection from the weather.

The front door opens to a elegant formal foyer, which offers unobstructed views of the palatial living room, the generous dining room, and the large kitchen.

Three large bedrooms and two updated bathrooms are on the second floor.  The third floor offers three additional bedrooms and one bathroom, and a fully equipped kitchen perfect as a guest suite, family suite, or rental.

''Washington Square''  has a swimming pool, broad lawns, magnificent trees, and a paved circular driveway with formal 2-car covered parking.
